description: Originally released in 2006, the 'Defining Moments Pack', also known as 'DMP', paired the AJ6 and AJ11 into a special release. Celebrating championship silhouettes that MJ wore, both shoes feature OG color blocking with gold accents. The 2023 iteration of the Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Gratitude' returns based on the 'Concord' colorway. Featuring a white tumbled leather upper and a black patent leather rand around the shoe, Metallic Gold accents can be found on the Jumpman logo on the heel and '23' stamped on the back. A Phylon midsole with Nike Air cushioning pairs with a carbon fiber shank plate and a clear rubber outsole.

Japanese brand TIGHTBOOTH works with Nike SB on a version of the Dunk Low SB. with a rich black suede upper enhanced by textured white leather forefoot and heel overlays. The reflective black leather Swoosh displays an orange TIGHTBOOTH tag while dual logos appear on the tongue. A black rubber midsole pairs with a contrasting white rubber outsole, while a playful mix of TIGHTBOOTH and Nike SB branding arrive on the orange insoles.

description: The Nike Dunk Low 'Team Gold' is a tribute to the classic 'Be True to Your School' series from 1985, featuring the iconic color blocking of that era. The shoe's low-profile upper is constructed from smooth leather and boasts a white base with dull yellow overlays and a matching Swoosh. The toe box features perforated detailing for increased ventilation, while comfy fit is delivered by the padded low-cut collar. The sneaker provides lightweight cushioning via a sturdy rubber cupsole with an interior foam wedge.

Like many other luxury brands, Louis Vuitton released its own take on the classic bumbag in the form of the Louis Vuitton Mini Bumbag Monogram. It features the Louis Vuitton monogram and is designed to be both fashionable and functional.

It comes with an adjustable gold chain that can be taken on and off based on when the bumbag will be worn and how it will be used.
